Uses of Package
org.microbean.configuration.cdi.annotation

  • Packages that use org.microbean.configuration.cdi.annotation 
    Package Description
    org.microbean.configuration.cdi.annotation
    Provides annotation classes and interfaces for helping to integrate the microBean Configuration framework into CDI.
  • Classes in org.microbean.configuration.cdi.annotation used by org.microbean.configuration.cdi.annotation 
    Class and Description
    Configuration
    An annotation—not a Qualifier—identifying a subspace within a larger configuration value space located in overall configuration space by configuration coordinates.
    Configuration.Literal
    An AnnotationLiteral representing a runtime instance of the Configuration annotation.
    ConfigurationCoordinate
    A repeatable annotation representing an individual configuration coordinate in a universe of such coordinates.
    ConfigurationCoordinates
    A Qualifier that houses individual ConfigurationCoordinate annotations.
    ConfigurationValue
    A Qualifier annotation indicating that the annotated element is related to a particular configuration value in some way.
    ConfigurationValue.Literal
    An AnnotationLiteral representing a runtime instance of the ConfigurationValue annotation.
